Sheeit. Yep I am sure he does. In my case I dont have innate regen as an AA and dont always have Regen as a Buff.<br>
<br>
&quot;On a velious BP, it's 10 stamin, 90hp, or 150hp. In just 3 ticks I make up the difference in HP. Unless you need a CH every 18 seconds, the fungi tunic is better.&quot;<br>
Since your set up gets you this regen rate it works for you. On me I would regen that amount in 3 times the timeframe as I frequently only had the regen rate the Fungi offered at 21 per tick.<br>
yes I can quite often need a Cheal every 54 seconds. Them PoP mobs are Brutal!<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Usually tho I found I was getting the Shaman 1950 heal tho, which was required earlier and more frequently than the Cheal.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dex is useless, ac is meaningless when compared to massive regen, str is overrated honestly, and the HP can be covered also by regen. &quot;<br>
Dex helps with weapon procs. Even an amount as small as +12 dex can be a significant amount. I guarantee you i proc at least once additional per combat while wearing the Cobalt BP.<br>
<br>
In retrospect, it looks like perhaps I could have rethought my AA strategy when I had the Fungi and went for Latent regen abilities instead of Durability/HP. And..i needed to be a Buff hound and get that regen buff! <br>
I went the route I did because I knew I was going to be upgrading to a Vindi Chestplate or even a Breastplate of Eradication and planned ahead for Massive HP in the 60+ game<br>
<br>
All I have been saying is that the Cobalt worked better in my position, and i really didnt notice the benefits of the Fungi until I was in Downtime. <br>
It has been a fun debate with you all. <br>
What it proves is that there are many viable routes all of us warriors can take to get to the top...choose the one that works for you.<br>
